cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.MA 

This paper focuses on the design of fog computing networks for the Tactile Internet, which involves low-latency and high-fidelity human-to-machine interactions. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses energy efficiency and optimization, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of optimization techniques and algorithms further suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the simulation of a self-driving bus system in a real-world scenario involving cellular network infrastructure suggests that it could also belong to cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
